  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting mandates\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk transactions\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential business license revocation\n\n5. Key Sectors Regulated:\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and regulatory mechanisms.",
